text:
Streatham Nandos is one of the smaller Nandos restaurants I have been to. The size is roughly 4000 to 5000 sqft ( do not qoute me on this as I have not seen the floor plan and my math isn't the greatest
.🙂 There is more or less window seating around the restaurant.

I went on a Sunday between 3-4pm. I was able to quickly get seats for two. The Streatham branch of Nandos uses a QR code option, so you can order from your table, which I find to be quick and effective. For those of you who are not tech savvy, you can still order in the usual manner.

The service was quick, the estimated time from ordering to receiving my food was around 10 mins.

Nandos food is, in my opinion, always cooked in a similar manner; so expect your favourite Menu option to be prepared according to the standards you have become accustomed to.

Overall, the experience was good, the environment was clean, and staff were attentive.

text: It's standard Nandoes fare and depending on who is churning out the grilled chicken you will get burnt as the marinade will add a bitter taste or you get an anemic chicken. Sadly as time has gone on the chicken has become poussin sized  but the price keeps increasing so you will leave hungry if you don't add sides to your order. Equally the sides size is also dwindling. The chips are served in a bowl and I can count the number. So sad that once someone buys an original company with a great reputation the next one buys it and chops into a franchise with sub par standards. Not good for disabled people as loo in cellar abd there is a step down level with no accessMercifully I only go with a friend when we meet up. I love Nando’s but this is the worst example of one. We arrived to a red hair lady and her colleague fighting (yes fighting!) at the grill and had to wait for him to storm off before someone came to seat us.
We watched our food wait under the heat lamps with lots of other food for a good 10 mins before it was brought over.
The food itself was wrong, I had to keep calling them back because the corn was missing, the halloumi was missing, etc.
I didn’t bother to try and have the other issues fixed but they were numerous: food was so dry, cheese was missing from the pittas, there was no mayo or sauce in the pittas, there was only a tiny bit of salad at the bottom of the pittas. The chips were cold. I could go on.
I’d give it a swerve if I were you. Brixtons a lot better.

text:
Visited Nandos Streatham for the first time today with my children but I won’t be coming back again.
Members of staff were very friendly, we waited for about 10 minutes to be seated, I placed our order using qr code, food was given to us as per order. Unfortunately 2 of the chicken thighs were not cooked properly - meat was pink! Spoke a member of the team who was very apologetic and offered to replace it straight away. Took a little while to cook and I had finished the rest of my food so the member of staff packed in a take away box for me. Got home stated eating and once again the meat was not cooked properly, only 1 piece out of the 4 was eatable. I drove back to Nandos and showed the chicken, again the member of staff was very apologetic and offered to replace the food again, I asked for a refund and this was given to me.
I have been to so many Nandos all over London and have never been served uncooked chicken!
Gave 3 stars as  the staff members were all so friendly but would of only given one otherwise.

Nandos is usually a solid choice, and I have generally had good experiences at this branch (both in person and as a takeaway). The worst thing though was the fact that our table was placed in a very awkward position in the way of everyone meaning we were constantly getting bumped, and it even caused a waitress to drop another tables drink order near us.

I don't like leaving negative reviews, but these are all problems that could be rectified by better management, so I'm hoping that the next visit to this branch is more positive.

text:
Don't bother getting food delivered from here, you will end up starving...
We had a movie night at home, so ordered food for delivery, they said it would be approx 35 mins. We live 5 mins drive from the branch, so after an hour waiting rang both, the branch and central customer services. After ringing the branch  (took about 15mins for them to pick the phone up), the guy said the food is on its way, it had left the restaurant about 2 mins before.
Meanwhile my bf kept holding on to customer services to provide some feedback. After another 10mins wait (about 25mins holding in total) he got through. Customer services also checked with the restaurant about the order and we were told that the food has NOT left the restaurant as its been busy. So we got different information and by that time were really hungry and rather frustrated. If we would have been informed about the delay or told that it was such a hassle getting it delivered, we would have gone to pick it up. As a result of the service received we told them not to bother with our order and refund the money. We ended up getting food from elsewhere.
Both, the false information provided (35mins should not be 1.5hr no matter what) and how the issue was handled has left us rather disappointed, havent experienced so rubbish service anywhere else. No more Nandos for a while, thats for sure.
title: Nando's Streatham

We normally find Nando’s reliable but this time the chicken was very disappointing. It was actually so overcooked that the meat was tough and dry through. Maybe eating in is better but we’ve had Nando’s takeaway from other branches before and they’ve been great. A real shame.

text:
Visited on 24/2/18 - very shocking. Walked in and had to wait for staff to finish their conversation before a manager made them aware they had customers waiting. Was escorted to a dirty table with food on it and around it. Ordered large fries - received large rice. One gentlemen was banging chairs as he was cleaning up, he then came up to me and told my table we have to leave at midnight. He told the table next to us the same thing and the customer complained as they had a lotof food left. After asking for the manager the same customer service assistant started shouting at the customer saying "You have to leave due to health and safety..."

All of this in front of his manager.

Long story short? Decent nandos food met by poor customer service!

text:
If I could give 0 I would.
This was the worse nandos experience I’ve ever had.
There were two people at the till and a line of about 9 people whilst there we’re other waiters walking around doing nothing! Which I didn’t understand at all.
I saw a chef drop chicken then pick it up snd put it back on a plate !
They were out of stock on about 15 items one which was the Mediterranean salad which is what I wanted. I was forced to order a ceaser salad as I am on a diet and am a type 1 diabetic and this was the only salad on offer. I clearly asked to have this salad with chicken breast.
When I received my food 20 minutes later , there was no chicken breast and it tasted revolting. The waiter had not put chicken breasts on my order which is what I clearly asked for. He then used the excuse he was tired!
Worset nandos ever i will not be returning ever and they will hear from my lawyer.

text:
Best Nando’s I’ve been to and that’s despite sometimes things going wrong.

1) Food here is very good quality and is consistently better than my local Nando’s.

2) When trying to place a telephone order on 2 occasions I could never get through, this happened today and they told me DND was accidentally selected on their phone, an inconvenience but nothing major. They dealt with it in a very professional manor I received a good will gesture after asking and they were extremely polite.

I highly recommend this branch of Nando’s for their caring nature about your custom and great quality food.

text: My aunt an I went there yesterday for afternoon lunch out. On arrival it was as busy as expected so we readied ourselves for a long wait...(I originally wanted 3 breast as I don't really like thigh or legs but was told that was not allowed). After ordering and making specific requests(Chicken well-done,large fries,two bottomless drinks) 1st mistake only one drink paid for.We paid again and sat chatting at our table  awaiting our order.About 15 mind later our order arrived-no large fries but a small single and the breast part of the chicken was undercooked!  Politely, I requested for the chicken to be redone and also enquired that we receive another fries-the waitress Social was very helpful and also apologetic. She said that she would get the fries and I can await a fresh piece  of breast chicken. The fries arrived,and because my aunts a diabetic she already started her me,so I began to eat what  I had in front of me.45 minutes later I finally got Sonia attention. I informed her that I was still waiting on my chicken breast!  Again very apologetic she assured me that a new peice of breast chicken would be cooked for me as I had experienced such problems. She reiterated breast, medium spicy and said because my meal was already complete would I like to take it away- to which I agreed.She also gave me extra fries for the inconvenience. Okay,when I got home,I opened the box to find though the top of the box indicates breast,a leg and thigh was inside!Waste of time effort and my hard earned monies. If I'd have known I would have gone to KFC...quarter of the price and I would get exactly what I asked for..1st try!....Seriously!
